on foreign relations mr truong_minh tam_will be visiting north america from may 2015 to june 2015 to advocate for human rights in vietnam mr tam_is former prisoner of_conscience who is also member of_the vietnam path movement accompany with mr tam_on this trip is pastor nguyen_manh hung member of_the interfaith council of_vietnam mobilized and_supported jointly by vietnam reform_party and_cambridge llp the delegation have_met and_exchanged talks with the vietnamese community in canada and_attended as guest speaker in parliament hearing in canada on in this hearing the delegation highlighted the truth about the human rights situation in vietnam with the first hand_experience and_witnessed as former prisoner of_conscience mr truong_minh tam_presented prison_conditions and_mistreatments of_jailed prisoners in political related cases some of_the prisoners referenced were dang xuan dieu nguyen dang minh_man and ta phong_tan whose situations have become dire adding great risks to their_health and_even their lives most critical was the 2014 death of_teacher dinh dang dinh a_prisoner of_conscience who passed away due to abusive mistreatments by the_regime and_irresponsible health care_system in prison the vietnam path_movement and_the interfaith council of vietnam demand the government of_vietnam to implement provisions in the international convention against_torture a_covenant in which vietnam is a_member we also urge the international_community and_the vietnamese people both_domestic and_abroad to support the_prisoners and_their families to overcome this difficult_time and_more importantly to fight for the freedom of_those who are still imprisoned for political reasons also on this trip the vietnam path movement asks the international community to pay more attention the harsh sentence of 16 years given to tran_huynh duy_thuc the founder of_the vietnam path_movement an_organization advocate_and fight for human rights in vietnam at last the vietnam path movement greatly_appreciates and_expresses our thanks to vietnam reform party for their effort to successfully_organize and_support this trip for mr truong minh_tam through this trip mr tam_can_deliver the truth to the public about prison conditions in vietnam as well as other mistreatments prisoners of_conscience have to_suffer
